('199803003008','Let $$P_n$$ denotes $$\\sum\\limits_{r=1}^{1}{r\\left( r+4 \\right)}=1\\left( 1+4 \\right)=5$$;;For n=1,;;$$\\begin{align};  & LHS=\\sum\\limits_{r=1}^{1}{r\\left( r+4 \\right)}=1\\left( 1+4 \\right)=5 \\\\ ; & RHS=\\frac{1}{6}\\left( 1 \\right)\\left( 1+1 \\right)\\left[ 2\\left( 1 \\right)+13 \\right]=5=LHS \\\\ ;\\end{align}$$;;$$P_1$$ is true;Assume $$P_k$$ is true for $$k\\in {{Z}^{+}}$$,;;i.e. $$\\sum\\limits_{r=1}^{k}{r\\left( r+4 \\right)}=\\frac{1}{6}k\\left( k+1 \\right)\\left( 2k+13 \\right)$$;For n=k+1;;$$\\begin{align};  & RHS=\\frac{1}{6}\\left( k+1 \\right)\\left[ \\left( k+1 \\right)+1 \\right]\\left[ 2\\left( k+1 \\right)+13 \\right] \\\\ ; & LHS=\\sum\\limits_{r=1}^{k+1}{r\\left( r+4 \\right)} \\\\ ; & =\\sum\\limits_{r=1}^{k}{r\\left( r+4 \\right)}+\\left( k+1 \\right)\\left( k+1+4 \\right) \\\\ ; & =\\frac{1}{6}k\\left( k+1 \\right)\\left( 2k+13 \\right)+\\left( k+1 \\right)\\left( k+1+4 \\right) \\\\ ; & =\\frac{1}{6}k\\left( k+1 \\right)\\left( 2k+13 \\right)+\\left( k+1 \\right)\\left( k+5 \\right) \\\\ ; & =\\frac{1}{6}\\left( k+1 \\right)\\left[ k\\left( 2k+13 \\right)+6\\left( k+5 \\right) \\right] \\\\ ; & =\\frac{1}{6}\\left( k+1 \\right)\\left[ 2{{k}^{2}}+19k+30 \\right] \\\\ ; & =\\frac{1}{6}\\left( k+1 \\right)\\left( k+2 \\right)\\left( 2k+15 \\right) \\\\ ; & =\\frac{1}{6}\\left( k+1 \\right)\\left[ \\left( k+1 \\right)+1 \\right]\\left[ 2\\left( k+1 \\right)+13 \\right]=RHS \\\\ ;\\end{align}$$;;$$P_{k+1}$$ is true if $$P_k$$ is true.;Therefore, by mathematical induction, $$P_n$$ is true for all $$n\\in {{Z}^{+}}$$'),
