('199904003009','Let n = sample size = 12;Let p = successful connection rate = 0.8;and q = 1- p = 0.2;Let X = no. of successful calls out of n;;$$X \\sim B(n,p)$$;$$P(X \\ge 9)$$;$$=P( X=9 ) + P( X=10 ) + P( X=11 ) + P( X=12 )$$;$$={}^{n}{C}_{9}{p}^{9}{q}^{n-9} + {}^{n}{C}_{10}{p}^{10}{q}^{n-10} + {}^{n}{C}_{11}{p}^{11}{q}^{n-11} + {}^{n}{C}_{12}{p}^{12}{q}^{n-12}$$;$$={}^{12}{C}_{9}({0.8})^{9}({0.2})^{3} + {}^{12}{C}_{10}({0.8})^{10}({0.2})^{2} + {}^{12}{C}_{11}({0.8})^{11}({0.2})^{1} + {}^{12}{C}_{12}({0.8})^{12}({0.2})^{0}$$;$$= 0.7946 = 0.795$$ (ans);;Let $${n}_{2}$$ = sample size = 120;Let $${p}_{s}$$ = sample success rate = $$\\frac{105}{120}$$ = 0.875;Let $${p}_{0}$$ = assumed success rate = 0.8 ;and $${q}_{0}$$ = 1 - $${p}_{0}$$ = 0.2;;Test $${H}_{0}$$ : p = $${p}_{0}$$ against $${H}_{1}$$ : p > $${p}_{0}$$;a 1- tailed test for improvement;The 4 % critical value, $${z}_{0.04} = 1.751$$;Reject $${H}_{0}$$ if $$z > {z}_{0.04}$$;Under $${H}_{0}$$, the test statistic is;$$z = \\frac{{p}_{s}-{p}_{0}}{\\sqrt{{p}_{0}{q}_{0}/{n}_{2}}} = \\frac{ 0.875 - 0.8}{\\sqrt{(0.8)(0.2)/120}} = 2.054$$;;Since $$z > {z}_{0.04}$$, reject $${H}_{0}$$ and conclude that at the 4% level of significance, there is sufficient evidence that the successful connection rate has improved.;;Let $${n}_{3}$$ = sample size = 150;$$\\hat{q} = \\frac{25}{150} = \\frac{1}{6}$$ and $$\\hat{p} = 1 - \\hat{q} = \\frac{5}{6}$$;$${z}_{0.04}\\sqrt{\\frac{\\hat{p}\\hat{q}}{{n}_{3}}} = 1.751\\sqrt{\\frac{(\\frac{5}{6})(\\frac{1}{6})}{150}} = 0.0533$$;;The 92% confidence interval for q is;$$\\left[\\hat{q} - {z}_{0.04}\\sqrt{\\frac{\\hat{p}\\hat{q}}{{n}_{3}}} , \\hat{q} + {z}_{0.04}\\sqrt{\\frac{\\hat{p}\\hat{q}}{{n}_{3}}}\\right]$$;$$=\\left[\\frac{1}{6} - 0.0533 , \\frac{1}{6} + 0.0533\\right]$$;$$=\\left[ 0.1134 , 0.2199\\right]$$;$$=\\left[ 0.113 , 0.220\\right]$$ (ans)'),
