('200103003012','$$\\sin 3\\theta = \\sin (2\\theta + \\theta)$$;$$= \\sin 2\\theta \\cos \\theta + \\cos 2\\theta \\sin \\theta$$;$$= 2\\sin \\theta \\cos ^{2} \\theta + (1 - 2\\sin ^{2}\\theta)\\sin \\theta$$;$$= 2\\sin \\theta(1 - \\sin ^{2}\\theta) + \\sin \\theta - 2\\sin ^{3}\\theta$$;$$=2\\sin \\ theta - 2\\sin ^{3}\\theta + \\sin \\theta - 2\\sin ^{3}\\theta$$;$$=3\\sin \\theta - 4\\sin ^{3}\\theta$$ (ans);;$$\\sin 3\\theta - \\cos 2\\theta$$;$$=(3 \\sin \\theta - 4\\sin ^{3}\\theta) - (1 - 2\\sin ^{2}\\theta)$$;$$=(3s - 4s^3) - ( 1 - 2s^2)$$;$$= - 1 + 3s + 2s^2 - 4s^3$$;$$=( 1 - s )(4s^2 + 2s - 1)$$ (ans);;With $$\\theta = 18^0$$,;$$\\sin 3\\theta = \\sin 3(18^0) = \\sin 54^0 \\equiv \\cos (90^0 - 54^0)$$;$$=\\cos 36^0 = cos2(18^0) \\equiv \\cos 2\\theta$$;;$$\\therefore \\theta = 18^0$$ is an exact solution of $$\\sin 3\\theta  = \\cos 2\\theta$$. (ans);;(i);$$\\sin 3\\theta = \\cos 2\\theta \\equiv \\sin 3\\theta - \\cos 2\\theta = 0$$;$$\\equiv ( 1 - s )(4s^2 + 2s - 1) = 0$$;where $$s = \\sin \\theta$$ and $$\\sin 18^0$$ is a solution.;$$\\Rightarrow s = 1$$ (NA, $$\\theta = 90^0$$);or $$s = \\frac{-2 \\pm \\sqrt{2^2 - 4(4)(-1)}}{2(4)} = \\frac{-2 \\pm \\sqrt{20}}{8}$$;$$=\\frac{1}{4}(-1 -\\sqrt{5})$$ (NA, $$\\sin 18^0 > 0$$ );or $$\\frac{1}{4}(-1 + \\sqrt{5})$$;$$\\therefore \\sin 18^0 = \\frac{1}{4}(-1 + \\sqrt{5})$$ (ans);;(ii);With $$\\theta = 234^0$$,;$$\\sin 3\\theta = \\sin 3(234^0) = \\sin 702^0$$;$$=\\sin (720^0 - 18^0) \\equiv \\sin -18^0$$;$$\\equiv \\cos (360^0 + 90^0 + 18^0) = \\cos 468^0$$;$$=\\cos 2(234^0) \\equiv \\cos 2\\theta$$;$$\\therefore \\theta = 234^0$$ is another exact solution of $$\\sin 3\\theta = \\cos 2\\theta$$.;Since $$\\sin 234^0 < 0$$, deduce that ;$$\\sin 234^0 = \\frac{1}{4}(-1 -\\sqrt{5})$$ (ans)'),
('200103003013','(a);(i) $$x > \\frac{2}{x}$$;$$x^3 > 2x$$;$$x^3 - 2x > 0$$;$$x (x^2 - 2) > 0$$;Critical values are $$ - \\sqrt{2}, 0, \\sqrt{2}$$;;img;;$$\\therefore$$ Solution is $$- \\sqrt{2} < x < 0$$ or $$x > \\sqrt{2}$$ (ans);;(ii)$$ |2x - 3| < |x + 1|$$;$$(2x - 3)^2 < (x + 1)^2$$;$$4x^2 -12x + 9 < x^2 + 2x + 1$$;$$3x^2 - 14x + 8 < 0$$;$$(3x - 2)(x - 4) < 0$$;$$(3x - 2) < 0$$ and $$( x - 4) > 0$$ or $$(3x - 2) > 0$$ and $$( x - 4) < 0$$;$$\\therefore x < \\frac{2}{3}$$ and $$ x > 4 $$ (NA);or $$\\frac{2}{3} < x < 4$$ (ans);;(b) $$3( 1! ) + 7( 2! ) + 13( 3! ) + ... + ( n^2  + n + 1 )( n! )$$;$$\\equiv \\sum \\limits_{r=1}^{n} (r^2 + r + 1)( r! )$$;Let $${P}_{n}$$ denote $$\\sum \\limits_{r=1}^{n} (r^2 + r + 1)( r! ) = ( n + 1 )^2 ( n! ) - 1$$;For n = 1,;LHS = $$(1^2 + 1 + 1)( 1!) = 3$$;RHS = $$(1 + 1)^2 ( 1! ) - 1 = 3 = LHS$$;$$\\therefore {P}_{1}$$ is true.;;Assume $${P}_{k}$$ is true for $$k \\in \\mathbb{Z}^{+}$$,;i.e $$\\sum \\limits_{r=1}^{k} (r^2 + r + 1)( r! ) = ( k + 1 )^2 ( k! ) - 1$$;For n = k + 1,;RHS = $$\\left[( k + 1) + 1\\right]^2 \\left[( k + 1 )!\\right] - 1$$;LHS = $$\\sum \\limits_{r=1}^{k+1} (r^2 + r + 1)( r! )$$;$$= \\sum \\limits_{r=1}^{k} (r^2 + r + 1)( r! ) + \\left[(k + 1)^2 + (k + 1) + 1\\right]\\left[( k + 1)!\\right]$$;$$= ( k + 1 )^2 ( k! ) - 1+ \\left[(k + 1)^2 + (k + 1) + 1\\right]\\left[( k + 1)!\\right]$$;$$=( k + 1 )\\left[(k + 1 )!\\right] - 1 + \\left[(k^2 + 2k + 1) + (k + 1) + 1\\right]\\left[( k + 1)!\\right]$$;$$=( k + 1 )\\left[(k + 1 )!\\right] - 1 + \\left[(k^2 + 3k + 3)\\right]\\left[( k + 1)!\\right]$$;$$=\\left[(k + 1) + (k^2 + 3k + 3)\\right]\\left[( k + 1)!\\right] - 1$$;$$=\\left[k^2 + 4k + 4\\right]\\left[( k + 1)!\\right] - 1$$;$$=\\left[k + 2\\right]^2\\left[( k + 1)!\\right] - 1$$;$$=\\left[(k+ 1) + 1\\right]^2\\left[( k + 1)!\\right] - 1 = RHS$$;$$\\therefore {P}_{k+1}$$ is true if $${P}_{k}$$ is true.;;Therefore by mathematical induction, $${P}_{n}$$ is true for all $$n \\in \\mathbb{Z}^{+}$$. (ans)'),
('200103003014','(a) Let $${r}_{1}$$ = common ratio of G.P. 1;Let $${r}_{2}$$ = common ratio of G.P. 2;$${r}_{2} = {{r}_{1}}^{2}$$;$${S}_{\\infty,1} = 16$$ and $${S}_{\\infty,2} = 64$$;;$$\\Rightarrow \\frac{a}{1-{r}_{1}} = 16$$ and $$\\frac{a}{1-{r}_{2}} = 64$$;$$\\Rightarrow a = 16(1 - {r}_{1})$$ and $$a = 64(1 - {r}_{2})$$;;Equating $$a$$:;$$16(1 - {r}_{1}) = 64(1 - {r}_{2})$$;$$(1 - {r}_{1}) = 4(1 - {{r}_{1}}^{2})$$;$$4{{r}_{1}}^{2} - {r}_{1} - 3 = 0$$;$$({r}_{1} - 1)(4{r}_{1} + 3) = 0$$;$${r}_{1} = 1$$ (NA) or $${r}_{1} = - \\frac{3}{4}$$;$$\\therefore a = 16\\left[1 - ( - \\frac{3}{4})\\right] = 28$$ (ans);;(b) Let $$a = 1^{st}$$ term of A.P;Let $$d$$ = common difference of A.P.;$$9^{th}$$ term, $${T}_{9} = 43$$;$$\\Rightarrow a + ( 9 - 1)d = 43$$;$$ a + 8d = 43$$              --------(1);Sum of $$1^{st} 15$$ terms, $${S}_{15} = 570$$;$$\\Rightarrow \\frac{1}{2}(15)\\left[2a + (15 - 1)d\\right] = 570$$;$$ a + 7d = 38$$              --------(2);;Eqn (1) - (2): $$d = 5$$;Subst into eqn (2):;$$ a + 7(5) = 38 \\Rightarrow a = 3$$;;Sum to $${n}^{th}$$ term, $${S}_{n} > 2265$$;$$\\Rightarrow \\frac{1}{2}(n)\\left[2(3) + (n - 1)(5)\\right] >2265$$;$$ n\\left[6 + 5n - 5\\right] > 4530$$;$$ 5n^2 + n - 4530 > 0$$;$$ 5n^2 + n - 4530 = 0$$;$$\\Rightarrow n =\\frac{-1 \\pm \\sqrt{1^2 - 4(5)(-4530)}}{2(5)} = \\frac{-1 \\pm 301}{10}$$;$$= - 30.2$$ (NA) or $$30$$;For $${S}_{n} > 2265$$,;least possible value of $$n = 31$$. (ans)'),
('200103003015','(a)$$\\int_{0}^{\\frac{1}{2}\\pi}\\frac{7\\cos x - 4\\sin x}{\\cos x + \\sin x}dx$$;$$\\equiv \\int_{0}^{\\frac{1}{2}\\pi}\\frac{\\frac{3}{2}(\\cos x + \\sin x) + \\frac{11}{2}(\\cos x - \\sin x)}{\\cos x + \\sin x}dx$$;$$= \\int_{0}^{\\frac{1}{2}\\pi}\\left[\\frac{3}{2} + \\frac{11}{2}\\frac{\\cos x - \\sin x}{\\cos x + \\sin x}\\right]dx$$;$$=\\left[\\frac{3}{2}x + \\frac{11}{2}\\ln (\\cos x + \\sin x)\\right]_{0}^{\\frac{1}{2}\\pi}$$ ;$$=\\left[\\frac{3}{2}(\\frac{1}{2}\\pi) + \\frac{11}{2}\\ln (0 + 1)\\right] - \\left[\\frac{3}{2}(0) + \\frac{11}{2}\\ln  (1 + 0)\\right]$$;$$=\\frac{3}{4}\\pi$$ (ans);;(b)$$\\int_{1}^{e}(\\ln x)^2dx$$;$$=\\left[x(\\ln x)^2\\right]_{1}^{e} - \\int_{1}^{e}\\left[x.2(\\ln x)\\frac{1}{x}\\right]dx$$;$$=\\left[e(\\ln e)^2 - (1)(\\ln 1)^2\\right] - 2\\int_{1}^{e}left[\\ln x]dx$$;$$=\\left[e - 0\\right] - 2\\left[x.(\\ln x)\\right]_{1}^{e} - 2\\int_{1}^{e}\\left[x.\\frac{1}{x}\\right]dx$$;$$=e - 2(\\left[e.(\\ln e) - (1)(\\ln 1)\\right] - \\int_{1}^{e}dx)$$;$$=e - 2(\\left[e - 0\\right] -\\left[e - 1\\right]) = e - 2$$ (ans);;(c) With $$x = \\frac{1}{y} \\equiv y = \\frac{1}{x}$$ , $$dx = -\\frac{1}{y^2}dy$$;$$\\int \\frac{1}{x\\sqrt{ x^2  - 1}}dx$$;$$\\equiv \\int \\frac{1}{\\frac{1}{y}\\sqrt{(\\frac{1}{y})^2 - 1}}( -\\frac{1}{y^2})dy$$;$$= - \\int \\frac{1}{\\sqrt{1- y^2}}dy$$;$$= - \\sin ^{-1}y + c$$, c = constant;$$= - \\sin ^{-1}\\frac{1}{x} + c$$ (ans)'),
('200103003016','Let $$O$$ = apex of pyramid;Let $$A$$,$$B$$,$$C$$,$$D$$ = corners of square base;Let $$P$$ = foot of perpendicular from O to base ABCD;Let $$M$$ = foot of perpendicular from O to edge AB;;img;;(i) Height of the pyramid is given by $$OP$$;$$OP = MP \\tan \\angle OMP = (\\frac{1}{2}a)\\tan 30^{\\circ}$$;$$= (\\frac{1}{2}a)(\\frac{1}{\\sqrt{3}}) = \\frac{a}{2\\sqrt{ 3}}$$ (ans);;(ii) Length of sloping edge is given by $$OA$$.;$$\\Delta OPM$$:;$$OM = MP / \\cos \\angle OMP = (\\frac{1}{2}a)/\\cos 30^{\\circ}$$;$$= (\\frac{1}{2}a)/(\\frac{\\sqrt{3}}{2}) = \\frac{1}{\\sqrt{3}}a$$;$$\\Delta OAM$$:;$$OA = \\sqrt{AM^2 + OM^2} = \\sqrt{(\\frac{1}{2}a)^2 + (\\frac{1}{\\sqrt{3}}a)^2 }$$;$$= \\sqrt{\\frac{1}{4}a^2 + \\frac{1}{3}a^2} = a\\sqrt {\\frac{7}{12}}$$ (ans);;(iii) Let $$N$$ = foot of perpendicular from $$B$$ to edge $$OC$$;Angle between two adjacent triangular faces is given by $$\\angle BND$$.;;$$\\sin \\angle NCB \\equiv \\sin \\angle OAM = \\frac{OM}{OA} = \\frac{\\frac{1}{\\sqrt{3}}a}{\\sqrt{\\frac{7}{12}}a} = \\sqrt{\\frac{4}{7}}$$;$$BN = BC\\sin \\angle NCB = \\sqrt{\\frac{4}{7}}a$$;$$DN \\equiv BN = \\sqrt{\\frac{4}{7}}a$$;;$$\\Delta BCD$$: $$BD^2 = BC^2 + CD^2 = a^2 + a^2 = 2a^2$$;Cosine rule on $$\\Delta BND$$:;$$BD^2 = BN^2 + DN^2 - 2.BN.DN.\\cos \\angle BND$$;$$2a^2 = \\frac{4}{7}a^2 + \\frac{4}{7}a^2 - 2(\\sqrt{\\frac{4}{7}}a)(\\sqrt{\\frac{4}{7}}a)\\cos \\angle BND$$;$$\\cos \\angle BND = - \\frac{3}{4}$$;$$\\angle BND = 138.6^{\\circ} = 139^{\\circ}$$ (ans)'),
('200103003017','(a) Let $$L$$ = length of cylinder = $$20x$$;When $$x = 5$$ , $$\\frac{dx}{dt} = 0.025$$;;(i) Rate of increase of length of cylinder,;$$\\frac{dL}{dt} = \\frac{d}{dt}[20x] = 20\\frac{dx}{dt}$$;$$= 20 (0.025) = 0.50 cms^{-1}$$;;(ii) Let $$V$$ = volume of cylinder = $$xL = 20x^2$$;Rate of increase of the volume of the cylinder,;$$\\frac{dV}{dt} = \\frac{d}{dt}[20x^2] = 40x\\frac{dx}{dt}$$;$$= 40(5)(0.025) = 5.0 cm^{3}s^{-1}$$ (ans);;(iii) Let $$r$$ = radius of the cylinder = $$\\sqrt{\\frac{x}{\\pi}}$$;Rate of increase of the radius of the cylinder,;$$\\frac{dr}{dt} = \\frac{d}{dt}[\\sqrt{\\frac{x}{\\pi}}] = \\frac{1}{2}\\sqrt{\\frac{1}{\\pi x}}\\frac{dx}{dt}$$;$$=\\frac{1}{2}\\sqrt{\\frac{1}{\\pi (5)}}(0.025) = 0.04954$$;$$= 0.0495 cms^{-1}$$ (ans);;(b);img;;Volume formed when $$R$$ is rotated about the $$x-axis$$, $${V}_{x}$$;$$=\\int_{0}^{\\frac{1}{4}\\pi}(\\pi {y}_{2}^{2} - \\pi {y}_{1}^{2})dx$$;$$=\\pi \\int_{0}^{\\frac{1}{4}\\pi}(\\cos ^{2}x - \\sin ^{2}x)dx$$;$$=\\pi \\int_{0}^{\\frac{1}{4}\\pi}\\cos 2xdx$$;$$=\\pi\\left[\\frac{1}{2}\\sin 2x\\right]_{0}^{\\frac{1}{4}\\pi}$$;$$=\\pi \\left[\\frac{1}{2} - 0\\right] = \\frac{1}{2}\\pi$$ (ans);;'),
