(b) is (iii) neither necessarily true nor necessarily false. ;Test $${H}_{0} : \\mu = 5$$ against $${H}_{1} : \\mu \\neq 5$$ a 2 tailed test for difference ;At 5% significance level, critical value $${z}_{0.025} = 1.960$$;$${H}_{0}$$ is rejected if $$| z | > | {z}_{0.025} |$$;$$ z < {z}_{0.025}$$ does not necessarily imply $$| z | > | {z}_{0.025} |$$ (ans)'),
