('200403003004','With $$t=\\sqrt{x+1}\\equiv {{t}^{2}}-1=x\\Rightarrow 2tdt=dx$$;At $$x=0,t=1$$; at $$x=3,t=2$$;$$\\begin{align};  & \\therefore \\int\\limits_{0}^{3}{x\\sqrt{x+1}dx} \\\\ ; & =\\int\\limits_{1}^{2}{\\left( {{t}^{2}}-1 \\right)t2tdt} \\\\ ; & =2\\int\\limits_{1}^{2}{\\left( {{t}^{4}}-{{t}^{2}} \\right)dt} \\\\ ; & =2\\left[ \\frac{1}{5}{{t}^{5}}-\\frac{1}{3}{{t}^{3}} \\right]_{1}^{2} \\\\ ; & =2\\left[ \\frac{31}{5}-\\frac{7}{3} \\right]=7\\frac{11}{15} \\\\ ;\\end{align}$$;'),
