('200403003007','$$y={{x}^{3}}{{e}^{x}}$$;Let $$P_n$$ denotes;$$\\frac{{{d}^{n}}y}{d{{x}^{n}}}={{e}^{x}}\\left( {{x}^{3}}+3n{{x}^{2}}+3n\\left( n-1 \\right)x+n\\left( n-1 \\right)\\left( n-2 \\right) \\right)$$;For n = 1,;$$\\begin{align};  & LHS=\\frac{dy}{dx}=\\frac{d}{dx}\\left[ {{x}^{3}}{{e}^{x}} \\right]={{e}^{x}}\\left( {{x}^{3}}+3{{x}^{2}} \\right) \\\\ ; & RHS={{e}^{x}}\\left( {{x}^{3}}+3{{x}^{2}} \\right)=LHS \\\\ ;\\end{align}$$;$$P_1$$ is true.;Assume $$P_k$$ is true for $$k\\in {{Z}^{+}}$$;i.e. $$\\frac{{{d}^{k}}y}{d{{x}^{k}}}={{e}^{x}}\\left( {{x}^{3}}+3k{{x}^{2}}+3k\\left( k-1 \\right)x+k\\left( k-1 \\right)\\left( k-2 \\right) \\right)$$;For n = k + 1,;$$\\begin{align};  & RHS={{e}^{x}}\\left( {{x}^{3}}+3\\left( k+1 \\right){{x}^{2}}+3\\left( k+1 \\right)\\left( k+1-1 \\right)x+\\left( k+1 \\right)\\left( k+1-1 \\right)\\left( k+1-2 \\right) \\right) \\\\ ; & LHS=\\frac{{{d}^{k+1}}y}{d{{x}^{k+1}}}=\\frac{d}{dx}\\left[ \\frac{{{d}^{k}}y}{d{{x}^{k}}} \\right] \\\\ ; & ={{e}^{x}}\\left( {{x}^{3}}+3k{{x}^{2}}+3k\\left( k-1 \\right)x+k\\left( k-1 \\right)\\left( k-2 \\right) \\right)+{{e}^{x}}\\left( 3{{x}^{2}}+6kx+3k\\left( k-1 \\right) \\right) \\\\ ; & ={{e}^{x}}\\left( {{x}^{3}}+3\\left( k+1 \\right){{x}^{2}}+3k\\left( k-1+2 \\right)x+k\\left( k-1 \\right)\\left( k-2+3 \\right) \\right) \\\\ ; & \\equiv {{e}^{x}}\\left( {{x}^{3}}+3\\left( k+1 \\right){{x}^{2}}+3\\left( k+1 \\right)\\left( k+1-1 \\right)x+\\left( k+1 \\right)\\left( k+1-1 \\right)\\left( k+1-2 \\right) \\right) \\\\ ; & =RHS \\\\ ;\\end{align}$$;;$$P_{k+1}$$ is true if $$P_k$$ is true.;Therefore, by mathematical induction, $$P_n$$ is true for all $$n\\in {{Z}^{+}}$$.;Deduce that, for n = 8,;$$\\begin{align};  & {{e}^{x}}\\left( {{x}^{3}}+3n{{x}^{2}}+3n\\left( n-1 \\right)x+n\\left( n-1 \\right)\\left( n-2 \\right) \\right) \\\\ ; & ={{e}^{x}}\\left( {{x}^{3}}+24{{x}^{2}}+168x+336 \\right) \\\\ ;\\end{align}$$;i.e.;\\[\\begin{align};  & {{e}^{x}}\\left( {{x}^{3}}+24{{x}^{2}}+168x+336 \\right)\\equiv \\frac{{{d}^{8}}y}{d{{x}^{8}}} \\\\ ; & \\therefore \\int{{{e}^{x}}\\left( {{x}^{3}}+24{{x}^{2}}+168x+336 \\right)dx} \\\\ ; & \\equiv \\int{\\frac{{{d}^{8}}y}{d{{x}^{8}}}dx}=\\frac{{{d}^{7}}y}{d{{x}^{7}}} \\\\ ; & \\equiv {{e}^{x}}\\left( {{x}^{3}}+3\\left( 7 \\right){{x}^{2}}+3\\left( 7 \\right)\\left( 7-1 \\right)x+\\left( 7 \\right)\\left( 7-1 \\right)\\left( 7-2 \\right) \\right) \\\\ ; & ={{e}^{x}}\\left( {{x}^{3}}+21{{x}^{2}}+126x+210 \\right) \\\\ ;\\end{align}\\]'),
('200403003008','Sketch diagram;img;;(i) ;Angle between line BH and plane BFGC is given by $$\\angle HBG$$;$$\\begin{align};  & \\vartriangle BCG: \\\\ ; & B{{G}^{2}}=B{{C}^{2}}+C{{G}^{2}}=89 \\\\ ; & \\vartriangle HBG: \\\\ ; & \\tan \\angle HBG=\\frac{HG}{BG}=\\frac{10}{\\sqrt{89}}=1.060 \\\\ ; & \\therefore \\angle HBG=46.67={{46.7}^{\\circ}}\\left( 1dp \\right) \\\\ ;\\end{align}$$;;(ii);Angle between planes AEGC and DHGC is given by $$\\angle ACD$$.;$$\\begin{align};  & \\tan \\angle ACD=\\frac{AD}{CD}=\\frac{8}{10}=0.8 \\\\ ; & \\therefore \\angle ACD=38.66={{38.7}^{\\circ}}\\left( 1dp \\right) \\\\ ;\\end{align}$$;;(iii) ;Angle between skew lines BG and HC is given by $$\\angle AHC$$.;(AH is parallel to BG and is in the same plane as HC);$$\\begin{align};  & \\vartriangle ABC: \\\\ ; & A{{C}^{2}}=A{{B}^{2}}+B{{C}^{2}}={{10}^{2}}+{{8}^{2}}=164 \\\\ ; & \\vartriangle CDH: \\\\ ; & C{{H}^{2}}=C{{D}^{2}}+D{{H}^{2}}={{10}^{2}}+{{5}^{2}}=125 \\\\ ; & AH=BG=\\sqrt{89} \\\\ ; & \\vartriangle AHC: \\\\ ; & A{{C}^{2}}=A{{H}^{2}}+C{{H}^{2}}-2.AH.CH.\\cos \\angle AHC \\\\ ; & \\Rightarrow \\cos \\angle AHC=1.3315 \\\\ ; & \\therefore \\angle AHC=76.29={{76.3}^{0}}\\left( 1dp \\right) \\\\ ;\\end{align}$$'),
('200403003009','(i) ;Positive odd integers, less than 1000, could be represented by:;2n - 1, n = 1, 2, 3, ... ,  500;i.e. No. of such integers, $$N_{odd}$$ = 500;;(ii) ;Positive odd integers, less than 1000, which are divisible by 5, could be represented by: ;5(2n - 1), n = 1, 2, 3, ... , 100;;i.e. No. of such integers, $$N_{odd}$$, 5 = 100;No. of positive integers, less than 1000, which are odd numbers and not divisible by 5:;$$N_{odd}$$, not 5  = $$N_{odd} - N_{odd}$$, 5 = 500 - 100 = 400;;Sum of the odd numbers, less than 1000, which are not divisible by 5;$$\\begin{align};  & =\\sum\\limits_{r=1}^{500}{\\left( 2r-1 \\right)}-\\sum\\limits_{r=1}^{100}{5\\left( 2r-1 \\right)} \\\\ ; & =2\\left[ \\frac{1}{2}\\left( 500 \\right)\\left( 500+1 \\right) \\right]-500-10\\left[ \\frac{1}{2}\\left( 100 \\right)\\left( 100+1 \\right) \\right]+5\\left[ 100 \\right] \\\\ ; & =200000 \\\\ ;\\end{align}$$'),
('200403003010','$$f:x\\mapsto \\frac{6x}{x+3},x\\ge 0$$;(i) Let y = f\'(x);$$\\begin{align};  & \\Rightarrow f\\left( y \\right)=x \\\\ ; & \\frac{6y}{y+3}=x \\\\ ; & 6y=x\\left( y+3 \\right) \\\\ ; & y\\left( 6-x \\right)=3x \\\\ ; & y=\\frac{3x}{6-x} \\\\ ; & \\therefore f\'\\left( x \\right)=\\frac{3x}{6-x} \\\\ ;\\end{align}$$;;(ii) Range of f, $${{R}_{f}}=\\left\\{ x:0\\le x\\le 6 \\right\\}$$;;(iii) Sketch $$y=\\frac{6x}{x+3},x\\ge 0$$;At x = 0, y = 0;$$f\\left( x \\right)=\\frac{6x}{x+3}\\equiv 6-\\frac{18}{x+3}$$;As $$x\\to \\infty ,f\\left( x \\right)\\to 6-0=6$$;img;;Equation of its asymptote is y = 6;;(iv) Shade bounded region (above):;img;;Area of bounded region (shaded);$$\\begin{align};  & =\\int\\limits_{0}^{6}{ydx}=\\int\\limits_{0}^{6}{\\frac{6x}{x+3}dx} \\\\ ; & \\equiv \\int\\limits_{0}^{3}{\\left( 6-\\frac{18}{x+3} \\right)dx} \\\\ ; & =\\left[ 6x \\right]_{0}^{3}-18\\left[ \\ln \\left( x+3 \\right) \\right]_{0}^{6} \\\\ ; & =36-18\\ln 3 \\\\ ;\\end{align}$$'),
('200403003011','a) ;$$\\begin{align};  & {{\\left( 1+y \\right)}^{8}}=1+8y+28{{y}^{2}}+56{{y}^{3}}+.. \\\\ ; & {{\\left( 1+x+k{{x}^{2}} \\right)}^{8}} \\\\ ; & ={{\\left( 1+x\\left( 1+kx \\right) \\right)}^{8}} \\\\ ; & =1+8x\\left( 1+kx \\right)+28{{x}^{2}}{{\\left( 1+kx \\right)}^{2}}+56{{x}^{3}}{{\\left( 1+kx \\right)}^{3}}+... \\\\ ; & =1+8x+8k{{x}^{2}}+28{{x}^{2}}\\left( 1+2kx+{{k}^{2}}{{x}^{2}} \\right)+56{{x}^{3}}\\left( 1+3kx+3{{k}^{2}}{{x}^{2}}+{{k}^{3}}{{x}^{3}} \\right)+... \\\\ ;\\end{align}$$;Coefficient of x3 = 0;$$\\begin{align};  & \\equiv 28\\left( 2k \\right)+56=0 \\\\ ; & \\Rightarrow k=-1 \\\\ ;\\end{align}$$;;b);$$\\begin{align};  & \\frac{{{\\left( 9+x \\right)}^{\\frac{1}{2}}}}{1+2x} \\\\ ; & \\equiv {{\\left( 9+x \\right)}^{\\frac{1}{2}}}{{\\left( 1+2x \\right)}^{-1}} \\\\ ; & \\equiv {{9}^{\\frac{1}{2}}}{{\\left( 1+\\frac{1}{9}x \\right)}^{\\frac{1}{2}}}{{\\left( 1+2x \\right)}^{-1}} \\\\ ; & =3\\left( 1+\\frac{1}{2}\\left( \\frac{1}{9}x \\right)+... \\right)\\left( 1-2x+... \\right) \\\\ ; & =\\left( 3+\\frac{1}{6}x+... \\right)\\left( 1-2x+... \\right) \\\\ ; & =3-\\frac{35}{6}x+... \\\\ ;\\end{align}$$;'),
