('200504003024','(i) Deduce that f(x) is symmetrical about x =1 $$\\Rightarrow$$Mode = 1;;(ii) f(x)$$\\geq$$0 for 0$$\\leq$$x$$\\leq$$2 - by definition $$\\Rightarrow$$ f(0)$$\\geq$$0;$$\\begin{align}  ;i.e. & a - b ( 0 - 1 )^2 \\geq 0 \\\\;&a - b \\geq 0 \\\\;&\\therefore a \\geq b\\\\;\\end{align}$$;;(iii) ;$$\\begin{align} ;& \\int^\\infty_{- \\infty} f ( x ) dx = 1 \\\\;& \\Rightarrow \\int^2_0 [ a - b(x - 1)^2 ] dx = 1 \\\\;& {[ ax - \\frac{1}{3}b ( x - 1 )^3 ]}^2_0 = 1 \\\\;& 2a - \\frac{2}{3}b = 1 \\\\;& 3a - b = \\frac{3}{2}\\\\;\\end{align}$$;;(iv) $$ b = \\frac{3}{8} \\Rightarrow 3a - \\frac{3}{8} = \\frac{3}{2} \\Rightarrow a = \\frac{5}{8}$$;If q is upper quartile of X, $$ \\int^q_{- \\infty} f ( x )d x = \\frac{3}{4}$$;$$\\begin{align}  ;\\\\ \\int^{\\sqrt{2}}_0 f(x)dx;\\\\ \\int^{\\sqrt{2}}_0 \\left[ \\frac{5}{8}- \\frac{3}{8}(x-1)^2 \\right] dx ;\\\\ = {\\left[ \\frac{5}{8}- \\frac{1}{8}(x-1)^3 \\right]}^{\\sqrt{2}}_0 ;\\\\ = \\left[ \\frac{5}{8}(\\sqrt{2})- \\frac{1}{8}(\\sqrt{2}-1)^3 \\right]-\\left[ 0- \\frac{1}{8}(-1)^3 \\right] ;\\\\ = \\frac{1}{8}\\left[ 5 \\sqrt{2}-(2 \\sqrt{2}-6 + 3 \\sqrt{2}-1)-(1) \\right] ;\\\\ = \\frac{6}{8}= \\frac{3}{4};\\end{align}$$;$$\\Rightarrow \\sqrt(2)$$ is upper quartile of X.'),
