('200603003006','Assume that $$ z^4 - 2z^3 + 6z^2 - 8z + 8 = 0 $$ has a root of the form $$ ki $$;$$\\begin{align}  ;\\Rightarrow (ki)^4 - 2(ki)^3 + 6(ki)^2 - 8(ki) + 8 = 0;\\\\ (ki)^4 - 2k^3i + 6k^2 - 8ki + 8 = 0;\\\\ (k^4 - 6k^2 + 8) + (2k^2-8)ki = 0;\\end{align}$$;;Equating Im parts:;$$ (2k^2 -8)k = 0 \\Rightarrow k =0 (NA) or K = \\pm 2$$ ;Equating Re parts:;$$ k^4 - 6k^2 + 8 = 0 $$;Subst $$ k = \\pm 2$$ into eqn:;LHS = $$(\\pm 2)^4 - 6(\\pm 2)^2 + 8 = 0$$ = LHS;$$ \\therefore z^4-2z^3+6z^2-8z+8=0 $$ has roots $$\\pm2i$$;;$$\\pm2i$$ are roots;$$ \\Rightarrow (z-2i)(z+2i) = (z^2 + 4) $$ is a factor;By long division:;$$ z^4 - 2z^3 + 6z^2 - 8z + 8 = 0$$;$$ \\equiv (z^2+4)(z^2 - 2z + 2) =0 $$;$$  z^2 -2z +2 =0$$;$$ \\Rightarrow z = \\frac{-(-2)\\pm\\sqrt{(-2)^2-4(1)(2)}}{2(1)} = 1\\pm i$$;$$ \\therefore z^4-2z^3+6z^2-8z + 8 =0 $$;$$ \\Rightarrow$$ z = i, -i, 1+i or 1-i'),
('200603003007','Let h = depth of liquid;Let r = radius of liquid surface;Let V = volume of liquid;;$$ \\frac{dV}{dt} = 2 cm^3s^-1$$;r = h $$ \\tan^{-1}{45^{\\circ}} $$ = h;;$$\\begin{align}  ;\\Rightarrow V = \\frac{1}{3}\\pi r^2 h = \\frac{1}{3}\\pi h^3 \\Rightarrow h = \\left(\\frac{3V}{\\pi}\\right)^{\\frac{1}{3}};\\\\ \\Rightarrow \\frac{dh}{dt} = \\frac{d}{dV} \\left(\\frac{3V}{\\pi}\\right)^{\\frac{1}{3}} x \\frac{dV}{dt} = \\frac{1}{\\pi}\\left(\\frac{3V}{\\pi}\\right)^{-\\frac{2}{3}}\\frac{dV}{dt};\\end{align}$$;;After 3 minutes, volume of remaining liquid, V = (initial volume) - (3min x run out rate) = 390 - 3 x 60 x 2 = 30 $$cm^3$$;$$ \\therefore $$ Rate at which depth is decreasing,;$$\\begin{align}  ;\\frac{dh}{dt} = \\frac{1}{\\pi}\\left(\\frac{3V}{\\pi}\\right)^{-\\frac{2}{3}}\\frac{dV}{dt} = \\frac{1}{\\pi}\\left(\\frac{3(30)}{\\pi}\\right)^{-\\frac{2}{3}}(2);\\\\ = 0.067996 = 0.0680 cms^{-1} (3sf) \\end{align}$$'),
