('200604003024','Let $$G_i = i^{th}$$ pupil in sample is a girl;Let $$B_i = i^{th}$$ pupil in sample is a boy;;$$\\begin{align}  ;P ( X = - 3 ) = P ( B_1 , B_2 , B_3 );\\\\ = \\frac{4}{10}\\cdot \\frac{3}{9}\\cdot \\frac{2}{8}= \\frac{1}{30};\\end{align}$$;;$$\\begin{align}  ;\\\\ P(X = - 1) = P(G_1, B_2, B_3) +P(B_1, G_2, B_3) +(B_1, B_2, G_3) ;\\\\ = \\frac{6}{10} \\cdot \\frac{4}{9} \\cdot \\frac{3}{8} +\\frac{4}{10} \\cdot \\frac{6}{9} \\cdot \\frac{3}{8} +\\frac{4}{10} \\cdot \\frac{3}{9} \\cdot \\frac{6}{8} ;\\\\ = \\frac{9}{30}= \\frac{3}{10};\\end{align}$$ ;$$\\begin{align}  ;\\\\ P(X = 1) = P(G_1, G_2, B_3) +P(G_1, B_2, G_3) +(B_1, G_2, G_3) ;\\\\ = \\frac{6}{10} \\cdot \\frac{5}{9} \\cdot \\frac{4}{8} +\\frac{6}{10} \\cdot \\frac{4}{9} \\cdot \\frac{5}{8} +\\frac{4}{10} \\cdot \\frac{6}{9} \\cdot \\frac{5}{8} ;\\\\= \\frac{15}{30}= \\frac{1}{2};\\end{align}$$;;$$\\begin{align}  ;\\\\ P(X = 3) = P(G_1, G_2, G_3) ;\\\\ = \\frac{6}{10}\\cdot \\frac{5}{9}\\cdot \\frac{4}{8};\\\\ = \\frac{5}{30} = \\frac{1}{6};\\end{align}$$;;$$ \\therefore $$Probability distribution of X is:;   img;;$$\\begin{align}  ;E ( \\lvert X \\lvert ) ;\\\\ = \\sum_{all  x} \\lvert x \\lvert P ( X = x ) ;\\\\ = 1 \\cdot(\\frac{9}{30}+\\frac{15}{30}) +3 \\cdot(\\frac{1}{30}+\\frac{5}{30}) ;\\\\ = 1.4 ;\\end{align}$$;;$$\\begin{align}  ;\\\\ E(\\lvert X \\lvert^2) ;\\\\ = {\\sum_{all  x}\\lvert x \\lvert}^2 P(X = x) ;\\\\ = 1^2 \\cdot ( \\frac{9}{30} +\\frac{15}{30} ) +3^2 \\cdot ( \\frac{1}{30} +\\frac{5}{30} ) ;\\\\ = 2.6 ;\\end{align}$$;;$$\\begin{align}  ;\\\\ Var ( \\lvert X \\lvert ) ;\\\\ = E ( \\lvert X \\lvert^2 ) - [ E ( \\lvert X \\lvert ) ]^2 ;\\\\ = 2.6 -(1.4)^2 ;\\\\ = 0.64;\\end{align}$$'),
('200604003025','Let n = no. of bags in sample = 80;Let $$\\mu=E(x)$$;Let $$\\sigma^2=Var(x)$$;;$$\\begin{align}  ;\\hat{\\mu} = \\overline{x} = \\frac{\\Sigma ( x - c )}{n} +c = \\frac{- 2510}{80} +10000 ;\\\\ = 9968.625 ;\\end{align}$$;$$\\begin{align} ;\\\\ \\hat{\\sigma}^2 = \\frac{1}{n - 1}\\left[ \\Sigma(x - c)^2 - \\frac{(\\Sigma(x - c))^2}{n}\\right] ;\\\\ = \\frac{1}{79} \\left( 2010203 - \\frac{( - 2510 )^2}{80} \\right) ;\\\\ = 24448.76 (2dp); \\end{align}$$;;Let $$\\mu_0$$ = required mean = 10 kg = 10000 g;Test $$H_0 : \\mu=\\mu_0$$ against $$H_1: \\mu<\\mu_0$$a 1-tailed test for less ;The 5% critical value, $$ z_{0.05} = 1.645 $$;Reject $$H_0$$ if $$ z < -z_{0.05}$$;Under $$H_0$$, the test statistic is ;$$\\begin{align}  z = \\frac{\\overline{x} - \\mu_0}{\\hat{\\sigma} / \\sqrt{n}} = \\frac{9968.625 - 100000}{\\sqrt{24448.76 / 80}} = - 1.794 \\end{align}$$;Since $$z < -z_{0.05}$$, reject $$H_0$$ and conclude that, at the 5% level of significance, there is sufficient evidence that the mean mass of the contents of a bag is less than 10 kg.;;The \'5%significance level\' refers to the probability that, by chance alone, the null hypothesis is rejected incorrectly, i.e. the null hypothesis is rejected although the sample is taken from a population in which the mean mass of the contents of a bag is 10 kg.'),
